# Project General Specifications

## Technology Stack
- Python 3.10
- Poetry for dependency management
- GitHub Actions for automated build and release
- Use GitHub as the code hosting platform
- Use Bash scripts

## Code Style
- Keep code concise and readable
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add appropriate comments to explain complex logic
- Follow the official style guide for each language

## Project Structure
- Maintain a clear project structure, adhering to modular principles
- Related functionalities should be placed in the same directory
- Use appropriate directory naming that reflects its content

## General Development Principles
- Write testable code
- Avoid repetitive code (DRY principle - Don't Repeat Yourself)
- Prioritize using existing libraries and tools; avoid reinventing the wheel
- Consider code maintainability and scalability

## Response Language
- Always reply to the user in English
